title: For Sale:  Interarms 50 Cal Hawken Rifle better sturdier than T/C Hawken
postcontent: First off, the quality on these is better than you are going to find on anything else. Unfortunately, our American companies like Thompson Center, Lyman, and Traditions are all producing cheaply made "traditional" muzzle loaders these days. The wood on those tends to have no grain or poor wood grain quality, and fit and finish is sloppy. Also they are using thinner brass on the furniture, and not finishing it out, especially on the patch boxes. On the Tradidtions I saw yesterday at Sportsman's Warehouse, the patch box is of minimum size, no depth to it, and bare wood on the inside, meaning no wood sealant was put on it to protect it from moisture, and the very thin brass door of the patch box certainly won't keep moisture out.  These Interarms Hawkens are SO MUCH BETTER in how they are made, everything is more sturdy, especially the brass furniture and wood quality. This one has a 29 inch , 66 twist barrel.  It has a very strong stock with good looking black mineral streaking lines that go down the full length of the stock. The buttstock is not skinny like on a lot of muzzle loaders at the local sporting goods stores. This normal thickness stock gives a wider footprint on your shoulder to mitigate recoil, meaning it will be a comfortable gun to shoot. The patch box is exceptional. It goes deep and has a lot of room for patches and primers, etc. It's not just decorative, it is every bit as functional as it is good looking, making it different and better than a lot of guns of this type. The brass furniture is excellent on this rifle, and so is the double set trigger. The sights are very good too. They are easy to use and practical in lower light. The only flaw is there are a few minor marks on the left side of the stock, and I put up two pictures of the left side showing them. A little buffing and then adding some  tung oil to the finish would probably take care of it. These rifles are $450 or more new. This one is $315. The only reason I am selling it is I want more money for bulding up a duck hunting boat for the fall season. It's a very well made rifle, and a great buy.
